----------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party data sources and attributions
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Open-Meteo (https://open-meteo.com)
  Forecast data is provided under CC-BY 4.0
  (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/). All tool responses
  that include weather data carry an `attribution` field reproducing
  the upstream credit string. Operators MUST surface that string to
  end users when displaying weather data.

JMA Disaster XML feed (https://xml.kishou.go.jp/)
  Issued by 気象庁 (Japan Meteorological Agency). Use is subject to
  the Japan Meteorological Business Act (気象業務法). The
  `get_weather_warning` tool caches data for at most 10 minutes and
  embeds an attribution + modification disclosure in every response.

eMAFF Fude Polygon (https://open.fude.maff.go.jp/)
  Public open data published by the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry
  and Fisheries. Snapshots are built locally by `npm run snapshots:build`
  and are NOT redistributed in this npm package.

FAMIC pesticide registrations (https://www.famic.go.jp/)
  Public data published by the Food and Agricultural Materials Inspection
  Center. Snapshots are built locally and NOT redistributed.

